Fix AOT warnings in 2 files by replacing `JsonSerializer` calls with AOT-safe alternatives.

**File 1: `/tmp/sv-5e09e752d2334406b37cfd05c4e0c598/before/ArmEnvironment.cs`**

Line 80 has: `public override string ToString() => JsonSerializer.Serialize(this);`

This uses reflection-based JsonSerializer. Replace it with a manual JSON string:
```csharp
public override string ToString() => $"{{\"Endpoint\":\"{Endpoint}\",\"Audience\":\"{Audience}\",\"DefaultScope\":\"{DefaultScope}\"}}";
```

Note: The `using System.Text.Json;` import at line 5 may no longer be needed after this change. Remove it only if no other code in the file references `System.Text.Json`.

**File 2: `/tmp/sv-5e09e752d2334406b37cfd05c4e0c598/before/ArmClientOptions.cs`**

Line 52 has:
```csharp
var allProfile = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>>(span);
```

Replace this with direct `JsonDocument` parsing. The data is a JSON object like `{"resource-manager": {"namespace": {"apiVersion": [...]}}}`. Replace lines 51-52:
```csharp
                var span = BinaryData.FromStream(stream).ToMemory().Span;
                var allProfile = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>>(span);
```
with:
```csharp
                var span = BinaryData.FromStream(stream).ToMemory().Span;
                using var profileDoc = JsonDocument.Parse(span);
                var armProfile = profileDoc.RootElement.GetProperty("resource-manager");
```

And then update the rest of the method to use `armProfile` directly as a `JsonElement` instead of `allProfile["resource-manager"]`. The current code after line 52 is:
```csharp
                var armProfile = allProfile["resource-manager"];
                foreach (var keyValuePair in armProfile)
                {
                    var namespaceName = keyValuePair.Key;
                    var element = keyValuePair.Value;

                    foreach (var apiVersionProperty in element.EnumerateObject())
                    {
                        ...
                    }
                }
```

Replace it with:
```csharp
                foreach (var keyValuePair in armProfile.EnumerateObject())
                {
                    var namespaceName = keyValuePair.Name;
                    var element = keyValuePair.Value;

                    foreach (var apiVersionProperty in element.EnumerateObject())
                    {
                        var apiVersion = apiVersionProperty.Name;
                        foreach (var resourceTypeItem in apiVersionProperty.Value.EnumerateArray())
                        {
                            string resourceTypeName = default;
                            foreach (var property in resourceTypeItem.EnumerateObject())
                            {
                                if (property.NameEquals("resourceType"))
                                {
                                    resourceTypeName = property.Value.GetString();
                                    break;
                                }
                            }
                            var resourceType = $"{namespaceName}/{resourceTypeName}";
                            ResourceApiVersionOverrides[resourceType] = apiVersion;
                        }
                    }
                }
```

Note the key changes:
- `allProfile["resource-manager"]` → `profileDoc.RootElement.GetProperty("resource-manager")`
- `foreach (var keyValuePair in armProfile)` → `foreach (var keyValuePair in armProfile.EnumerateObject())`  
- `keyValuePair.Key` → `keyValuePair.Name`
- `keyValuePair.Value` stays the same (JsonElement in both cases)
- Remove the line `var armProfile = allProfile["resource-manager"];` since it's merged

Also, the `using System.Collections.Generic;` import at line 5 may no longer be needed if no other code uses `Dictionary` or other generic collections. Check before removing. Actually, `ResourceApiVersionOverrides` is `IDictionary<ResourceType, string>` so collections import is still needed.

The `using System.Text.Json;` import is still needed for `JsonDocument` and `JsonElement`.

Use the `edit` tool. Read each file first with `view`, then apply changes.

